HEADWORD: Selachostomi
<hw>Sel`a*chos"to*mi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Selachii</er>, and <er>Stoma</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of ganoid fishes which includes the paddlefish, in which
the mouth is armed with small teeth.</def>⟦br⟧
